narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: The Academic Coaching Workshop gave me a boost in my college application by prompting me to research prospective colleges earlier and create a college grid that will be a useful reference during the application. Working on the activity list and getting feedback on that will also help with that part of the Common App. But perhaps most useful of all was the little quizzes we had to determine what kinds of learners we were. They helped me learn new studying strategies (which I've already found useful), use effective strategies I was already using more confidently, and get rid of or modify strategies that weren't benefiting me very much.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
The material taught was highly relevant to the name of the course. It covered all the important areas in just 6 classes: the college application, the quizzes to determine what kinds of learners we were, studying strategies, note-taking strategies, exam-taking strategies, and so much more!
One of the things that could be improved is for the instructor to stay more up-to-date with the current (or most recent) Common App to provide the most accurate information about how things should be handled. It must be mentioned, however, that even if this is not done, most of the information is beneficial and the other minor details can be easily dealt with by the applicants themselves.
As an afterthought, I understand that time is a barrier, but would it help for students to also learn about the Coalition Application a little? If not in class, at least as a worksheet/leaflet for students to go through after the course/in their own time?

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Of course! For the very reasons I mentioned in my answer to the first question. I feel like lots of students, especially in schools (like mine) that don't have an official counselor, will find this course extremely helpful; in fact, I'm confident this course may be the difference between getting accepted or rejected from a certain college!

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
